external_knowledge:
- Researchers are individuals who access school performance data for analysis purposes; 
- Access since the beginning of 2023 refers to any access date on or after January 1, 2023; 
- Top three performing schools are those with the highest math scores within each school type and low-income percentage category; 
- School types include elementary, middle, and high schools; 
- Low-income percentages represent the proportion of students from low-income families in each school.

sql:
SELECT user_name, email
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (SELECT user_id FROM data_requests);

SELECT total_students
FROM school_districts
WHERE district_name = 'Shelbyville District';

SELECT district_id, COUNT(school_id) AS number_of_schools
FROM school_district_membership
GROUP BY district_id;

